Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.29,0:00:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}上溯至宇宙初始 周遭还只是一片漆黑{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In the beginning, there was darkness.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.62,0:00:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不知何时 忽地一声巨响{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And then... Bang!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.69,0:00:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}时间空间以及物质皆由此发端{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Giving birth to an endless expanding existence{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.49,0:00:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}此后不断膨胀 延伸 永无止境{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}of time, space, and matter.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.02,0:00:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每一天 新的发现都在不断为我们解开{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Every day, new discoveries are unlocking{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.48,0:00:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}蕴藏于这里的那些神秘莫测{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the mysterious, the mind-blowing,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.60,0:00:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}令人大开眼界 致命的秘密{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the deadly secrets of a place we call{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.61,0:00:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们称这个地方为"宇宙"{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the universe.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.13,0:00:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳系{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The Solar System.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.86,0:00:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它是如何在星际混乱的湮没中形成的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}How did it emerge from the oblivion of interstellar chaos?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.93,0:00:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们是由气体和灰尘组成的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We are made of gas and dust.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.08,0:00:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}今日太阳和行星中藏有它们的身世奇迷{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Today the sun and planets hold fascinating clues to their origins{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.21,0:00:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们起源于一团极其微小而不可见的颗粒{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}in a haze of particles so small, they're virtually invisible.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.37,0:00:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们过去的证据 就在我们周围{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The evidence of our past is all around us.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.99,0:00:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}然而 创造出太阳系的巨大力量{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But are the titanic forces that created our Solar System{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.28,0:00:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在整个宇宙中是常见的吗{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}common throughout the universe?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.45,0:00:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还是我们是特殊的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Or are we unique?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.36,0:00:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的太阳系似乎是很特殊的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Our Solar System seems to be one of the oddballs.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.57,0:01:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙也许有无数方式来创造恒星和行星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The universe may have countless strategies for crafting stars and planets,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.26,0:01:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是仅有一法能够决定太阳系的形成{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}but only one could determine how the Solar System was made.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.56,0:01:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳系约在46亿年前开始形成{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It begins at a point in time nearly 4.6 billion years ago.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.28,0:01:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一大团气体云诡异地在{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}A giant cloud of gas and dust floats eerily{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.82,0:01:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}银河偏远的旁支漂浮{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}through a remote arm of the Milky Way,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.10,0:01:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}其温度为零下四百余度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}chilled to more than 400 degrees below zero.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.58,0:01:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当它独自在那儿{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}When it's sitting there all alone{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.23,0:01:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这团分子云中 没什么会发生{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}nothing much is happening in a molecular cloud.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.85,0:01:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它的温度很低{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The temperatures are very low.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.18,0:01:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那些粒子移动得非常缓慢{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The particles are moving around very, very slowly.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.82,0:01:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}几乎就是静止不动{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's just sitting there.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.34,0:01:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但若附近有一颗超新星 即爆炸的恒星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But if you have a nearby supernova, an exploding star,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.58,0:02:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它就会释放冲击波穿过这团分子云{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}it can send a shockwave through this molecular cloud...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.46,0:02:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从而触发了引力坍缩{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}triggering its gravitational collapse.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.06,0:02:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这种坍缩是长期过程中的第一步{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}That collapse is the first step in a long process{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.39,0:02:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这个过程促使了现在太阳系的形成{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that brings the place we now call the Solar System into existence.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.45,0:02:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}现在我们要跟随其最初7亿年的时间线{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Our mission now will be to follow a timeline of the first 700 million years,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.52,0:02:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在这段时间内 太阳系形成并趋于稳定{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the epoch in which the Solar System formed and stabilized.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.65,0:02:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们先来看看如今的太阳和其行星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We start by looking at the Sun and its planets as they are today.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.90,0:02:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们过去的证据 就在我们周围{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The evidence of our past is all around us.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.38,0:02:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在内太阳系的四颗行星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The four planets in the inner part of the Solar System{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.68,0:02:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}由岩石和金属组成{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}are made of rock and metal,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.10,0:02:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而外太阳系的四颗行星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and the four planets in the outter part of the Solar System{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.43,0:02:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}则是巨大的气体星球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}are these giant balls of gas.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.19,0:02:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}很明显 太阳系的形成经历很多不同的过程{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So clearly, different processes were at play,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.46,0:02:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这也表明了我们是如何走到这一步的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and that tells us something about how we got here.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.43,0:03:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们所知情形和现在科学家相信发生的无异{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We learn the story as scientists presently believe it happened,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.95,0:03:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它发生于太阳系诞生的伊始{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}from time zero, the very beginning of our Solar System.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.28,0:03:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}超新星爆炸不仅给这巨大的气体云团{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The supernova explosion not only seeds the giant gas cloud{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.16,0:03:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}带来了铁和铀这类重元素{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}with heavy elements like iron and uranium,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.41,0:03:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}爆炸带来的震动将这团云推向了未来{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the jolt of the explosion gives the cloud a push into the future,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.99,0:03:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}波前锋将云团的气体压缩成一种临界物质{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}as wave fronts compress the cloud's gases into a critical mass.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.88,0:03:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在引力作用下 这一团物质开始坍缩{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}That mass begins to collapse under the force of gravity,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.65,0:03:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}该过程无法停止 急速并且不可逆转{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and then it's unstoppable. It's rapid, it's irreversible.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.28,0:03:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就像过山车达到轨道顶端{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's like a roller coaster reaching the top of its track{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.63,0:03:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}然后急速冲下另一边一样{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and speeding down the other side.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.98,0:03:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这个注定要成为太阳系的坍缩云团{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The collapsing cloud destined to become our solar System{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.98,0:03:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}成为了一座混沌运动的主题公园{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}becomes a virtual theme park of chaotic motion.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.45,0:03:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}像北仙乐园这样的游乐园很适合让人们{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}An amusement park like North Fairy Farm is a great place to people to come{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.58,0:04:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}体验那种早期太阳系形成时的运动现象{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and experience a kind of a motion that happens in the early solar system.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.37,0:04:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有引力 碰撞 动力 推力{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}There's gravity. There's collisions, momentum, forces.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.52,0:04:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在早期太阳系里发生的所有作用{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}All of those interactions that took place in the early Solar system{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.73,0:04:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都能在这里的不同游乐项目中体现出来{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}can be found here on all the different kinds of rides.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.26,0:04:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在迅速坍缩的云团中 相互作用更为激烈{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Those interactions intensify in the rapidly collapsing cloud,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.43,0:04:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}气体和灰尘密集形成致密区域{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}where gas and dust contracts into dense pockets.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.86,0:04:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每一片区域都是恒星的温床{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Each will become the nursery of a star.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.65,0:04:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当巨大的分子云被触发并且开始坍缩{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}When the giant molecular cloud was triggered and started to collapse,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.24,0:04:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}很多原恒星和很多太阳系{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}a lot of other protostars and a lot of other solar systems{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.49,0:04:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也都同时诞生了{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}were formed at the same time.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.14,0:04:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所以太阳的周围其实有许多{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So our Sun actually has a lot of brother and sister stars{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.35,0:04:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}兄弟姐妹恒星 他们也在那时诞生{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that formed right around the same time as the Sun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.46,0:04:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳系形成的第一阶段{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The first stages of our Solar System's creation{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.32,0:04:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并不特殊{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}are hardly unique.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.41,0:04:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如今我们看到同样的事情发生在猎户座星云{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Today we witness the same thing happening in the Orion constellation,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.61,0:04:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一团巨大的分子云 延展数百光年{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}where a giant molecular cloud stretches hundreds of light years across.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.57,0:05:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}其中 坍缩区域正在孕育年轻的星球群{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In some places, collapsing pockets are now forming clusters of young stars,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.80,0:05:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们照亮了周围的气体{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}which light up the surrounding gas.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.53,0:05:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}游乐场中的环形运动{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The circus of motions in the amusement park{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.55,0:05:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}巧妙地模拟了构成太阳系的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}aptly parallels the movements of space matter{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.33,0:05:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太空物质的运动{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that comes together to make the Solar System.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.41,0:05:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些运动中最基本的是圆周运动{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The most basic of these motions is circular,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.15,0:05:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就像天空旋转木马{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}like a celestial carousel.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.86,0:05:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当前太阳系云团坍缩时{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}As the pre-solar cloud collapses,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.43,0:05:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们开始注意到它的旋转{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}we begin to notice its rotation,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.62,0:05:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这个旋转其实从一开始就存在{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}a spin that's actually been there from the beginning.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.57,0:05:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}整个星系都在旋转{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The entire galaxy rotates.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.40,0:05:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}星系中的所有物质都在旋转{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Everything in the galaxy rotates.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.06,0:05:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每种物质相对于其它物质都在旋转{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Everything is rotating with respect to everything else.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.98,0:05:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所以旋转是恒星坍缩物理学的重要部分{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And so rotation is part and parcel to the physics of... of stellar collapse.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.80,0:05:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}接下来发生的 就如同旋转的冰上选手{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}What happens next resembles a spinning ice skater.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.11,0:06:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当她收起胳膊 便旋转得更快{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}When she draws in her arms, she spins faster.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.52,0:06:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当引力将云团中的气体聚集{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}As gravity draws in the cloud's gas,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.05,0:06:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}云团不仅仅旋转得更快{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the cloud not only spins faster...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.77,0:06:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不可避免的 它形成了碟形{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It inevitably flattens into a disc.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.26,0:06:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们在地球上也能看到类似的过程{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We can see a similar process at work on Earth.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.40,0:06:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在加州的乔·卡里亚蒂玻璃吹制工作室{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In places like Joe Cariati's glass blowing workshop in California,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.50,0:06:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}天文学家劳拉·丹利正在观察吹制过程{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}where astronomer Laura Danly is observing the action.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.04,0:06:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}乔先取出一团红热的液态玻璃{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Joe begins with a round blob of red-hot molten glass.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.18,0:06:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}其实我们就是拿出一个圆形实体{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We basically just are taking a solid mass that was round{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.01,0:06:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}然后旋转它{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and spinning it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.01,0:06:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它变得扁平是因为液体{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It flattens because it's much easier for the fluid,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.67,0:06:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也就是液态玻璃{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the fluid of this liquid glass,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.18,0:06:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}更容易围绕着旋转轴坍缩{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}to collapse in the same axes along the axes of spinning{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.36,0:06:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而不是抗拒旋转和角动量{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}rather than try to fight the spin{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.45,0:06:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}向中心聚集{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}or fight the angular momentum and move closer.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.68,0:06:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}正如我们的太阳系 若行星在此形成{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And just like in our Solar System, if there were planets forming in there,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.28,0:06:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们会在同一个平面上{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}they'd all be in the same plane.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.30,0:07:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就像是我们的太阳系原行星盘一样{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's just like the disc of our Solar System.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.51,0:07:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}现在 它看起来是个椭圆 而非圆形{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Now, it looks kind of elliptical. It's not circular.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.78,0:07:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们认为太阳系的圆形的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We think of our own Solar System as being circular.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.98,0:07:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是我记得你告诉过我 原因是一边偏重{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But I think you told me it had to do with there being more mass on one side.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.38,0:07:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所以这也许有点像双子星的形成{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So maybe it's kind of like an analog of a binary star forming,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.23,0:07:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也就是 质量大一点的一边{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}where you've got maybe extra mass on one side that's{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.34,0:07:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}会形成恒星或褐矮星 又或者{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}also going to form into a star or a brown dwarf or maybe a...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.66,0:07:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一颗非常重的 类似木星的行星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}just a very massive Jupiter-like planet.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.14,0:07:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}真想摸摸它 但估计是个坏主意{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's so tempting to touch it, but I imagine it's a bad idea.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.89,0:07:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不 我们不能碰它 真的不能碰{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Oh, no, we can't do that. Yeah. We can't do that.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.34,0:07:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}时间到十万年时{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}100 thousand years after it began,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.25,0:07:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将要变为太阳系的云气彻底塌缩{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the cloud that would become our Solar System is almost entirely collapsed{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.93,0:07:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}云气中心被逐渐形成的原恒星照亮{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and its center is glowing with the radiance of an emerging protostar.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.82,0:07:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}原恒星是恒星最原始的状态{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}A protostar is the very early state as of becoming a star,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.49,0:07:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那时恒星仍在塌缩{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}when the star is still collapsing down{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.28,0:07:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}辐射到周围的能量正来自于{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and the energy that is radiating out{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.47,0:07:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那种引力坍缩{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}is coming from that gravitational collapse.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.04,0:08:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}恒星仍将升温 因为其体积在缩小{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's still getting hotter because it's getting smaller.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.97,0:08:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}恒星的形成过程{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's not doing the nuclear reactions{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.18,0:08:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}其核心阶段与核反应过程是不同的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}like a star will be doing when it's in its main phase of being a star.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.57,0:08:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}出现的原恒星开始吞噬{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The emerging protostar begins gobbling up the disc of gas and dust{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.83,0:08:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}组成太阳星云的气体和灰尘{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that makes up what's called the solar nebula.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.89,0:08:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大部分云气都变成了太阳的一部分{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So much of it will end up in the Sun,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.78,0:08:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}余下给行星 月球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}then what's left over for the planets, moons,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.55,0:08:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}星子 甚至我们身体的部分 非常少{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}asteroids, and even our own bodies is so meager,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.02,0:08:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就像宇宙的施舍一样{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}it's almost a cosmic afterthought.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.91,0:08:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们住在一颗行星上{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We happen to live on a planet,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.82,0:08:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所以行星的组成成分对我们很重要{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}so the stuff that went into making the planet is very important to us.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.83,0:08:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但这仅仅是整体的一小部分而已{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But it was just a tiny part of the whole mix.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.86,0:08:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这个停车场很好地说明了这一部分有多渺小{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}This parking lot is a good way of showing how tiny.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.94,0:08:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在如今的太阳系中{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}When you look at the Solar System today,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.06,0:08:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳占了总质量的99.85%{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the sun is 99.85% of the total mass.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.13,0:08:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在停车场里的500辆车之中{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So compared with the 500 cars in this parking lot,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.52,0:08:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我的车就和所有剩给{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}my car is just about all that's left over{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.28,0:09:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}行星 星子 和月球的成分一样{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}for all the planets, asteroids, and moons.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.52,0:09:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}至于分给地球的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And as for the earth itself, well,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.31,0:09:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就和这个备胎分量一样 仅此而已{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that might be comparable to this spare tire, nothing bigger.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.30,0:09:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一百万年之后{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}At 1 million years after time zero{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.40,0:09:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳系对行星建构材料的分类{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the Solar System's method for sorting out{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.56,0:09:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}已经很明确了{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}its planet building material is clear,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.50,0:09:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}根据温度 它们分布在原行星盘的不同区域{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}they're separated by the different temperatures in the disc.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.87,0:09:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}靠近原太阳的地方{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Close to the protosun,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.08,0:09:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}两千度的高温 蒸发了所有物质{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}temperatures above 2,000 degrees vaporize everything.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.33,0:09:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}然而 在约八百万公里处 是岩石带{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But about 5 million miles out lies the rock line,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.70,0:09:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这里足够冷 让金属和矿物质固化{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}where it's cool enough for metals and minerals to turn solid.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.89,0:09:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}更远的区域是冰雪带{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Much farther out lies the snow line,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.07,0:09:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这儿最冷可达零下三百七十五度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}where it's as much as 375 degrees below 0,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.01,0:09:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}冷到能让水 甲烷和氨冷冻成冰{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}cold enough for water, methane, and ammonia to freeze into ices.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.97,0:10:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}早期的太阳系 和做棉花糖相似{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The early Solar System is a little bit like making cotton candy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.92,0:10:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为了演示如何做棉花糖{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And to show us how cotton candy is made,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.85,0:10:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们请凯西·吴 来为我们做美味糖果{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}we have Kathy Woo here to make us a delicious treat.{\r}
